The Appeal court sitting in Port Harcourt has set aside the judgment of the Rivers State Governorship Election Petition Tribunal that dismissed the petition of the Governorship Candidate of the AAC, Biokpomabo Awara for abandoning their petition. The five man panel consequently directed all parties to return to the tribunal to hear the matter on its merit. The judgment read by Justice J.O BADA disclosed that the appellant did no harm for requesting the regularization of his suit. More Details… Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.